cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a new CNN module for left ventricle segmentation from cine MRI that incorporates temporal information using optical flow. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. Additionally, the use of dilated convolution suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) category. The application of the proposed method to medical imaging further suggests that it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) category. Finally, the use of a neural network for segmentation suggests that it may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) category.
